time required: 20m
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince is cooked, add the @Thai style spice mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g}. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @ketjap manis{25%ml} and @water{25%ml} for the pork.

Stir together until slightly thickened and nicely glazed, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

A couple of minutes before you're ready to serve, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Transfer the tortillas to your #plates{}.

Spread the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} onto each one.

Share the baby gem between your tortillas.

Top with the glazed pork and cucumber - as much as you'd like.

Sprinkle with the peanuts to finish.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!